Some selections might have taken longer to be propagated, but as the whole kafka cluster was intermittent, it’s hard to tell exactly. But in the end of the day all the selection was done

> is there a way that we would’ve been able to catch it on our side with monitoring?
You have seem a spike of your fallback meal selection request, but there’s nothing much to be done. As PCS works async, this shouldn’t be a big deal for customers

where do you see the spike?
